Description: Fragment of round handle with gradual curve of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Production date: 213 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Charmokles. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 163, 27
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0653)
